I can't give a review about using this as a foundation, but if you're looking for a cream contour product I highly recommend trying this.

name: maaya
review:
I bought this because I wanted a convenient foundation to put on when I traveling. I have oily skin and so wasn't expecting much but was pleasantly surprised. I would have given this a 5-star except that I can't testify how it holds up to oily skin in summer, since it's fall/winter now.

The coverage is medium and buildable; I was happy that I could build coverage without it being cakey. It stayed matte during the day and didn't "break" on my nose, as most foundations do (though, again, it's fall/winter now). It blends well, even with fingers. The shade I got was an EXACT match, which is impressive (usually they're too yellow or too pink).

The only downside is that it's small; 2/3 of the tube is the rotating part, not the part that actually encloses the stick. I mean... if only 1/3 of the tube is the actual product, then they could have made the rotating part shorter, or lowered the price!

name: char
review: I'm so glad I found this. It's quick, natural feeling and natural looking. For those of you who have trouble blending this product, apply the foundation and spray a setting spray. I use the rose water spray (my skin is oily and red, but you can use whichever one) don't saturate it though! Just a couple of sprays and blend with the brush. I find it to be a lot easier but I almost never need to use the spray. Other than that it's amazing

name: Miss Keri
review: I love this product. I don't have to wear a concealer if I choose not to. All day coverage with little to no touch up. Matches my skin tone extremely well.

*i did find this product to have a drying effect on my skin, so if you are already a dry skinned person, this may not be the best product for you.

review: I disliked it in general.

review: I use this product everyday and it's my favorite concealer!

review: I think it could cover more and I wish I would have brought a lighter color for under my eyes

name: Dana
review: I really liked this product. It provided full coverage without settling into the fine lines.

name: Sunny
review:
I use this over a mineral sunscreen as a concealer / light foundation. It covers fairly well, stays reasonably matte, and does not irritate my sensitive skin. Three of the shades work pretty well with my fair skin without looking pasty. I love the extra sun protection it gives, and it's fantastic for travel.

On the down side, it goes on a tiny bit dry for me. I would definitely need a good moisturizer underneath if I were not already using my sunscreen. It doesn't hold up more than 6-8 hours, but that seems like a fair trade-off for such light and natural-looking coverage.

name: Little Red
review: I don't think I get flawless coverage - I really think there's no such thing as flawless - but I still get pretty darn good coverage.  I usually have to do a couple touch-ups throughout the day, but overall, I like this.

name: AS
review: I have problems finding a makeup that blends with my fair skin (blonde hair & green eyes) but yet is not greasy or oily.  This is the best makeup I have found.  No liquid mess, no oily greasy transfer to clothes.  This is so easy to apply and I use it every day as my foundation.  I just apply to cheeks, nose, chin, forehead and blend.  It blends amazingly with my skin and there is no line along my chin.  I have combination skin and this has not clogged my pores or caused any break outs.  The best part is it has 20 spf in it so I am protecting my skin and looking great!

name: rbkh
review: this concealer is great for spots as it goes on creamy and covers redness.  Downside is that is has absolutely no staying power and disappears in about an hour; also, it tends to break up around areas you may move/touch often like around the eyes, mouth, nose, and chin. if you don't mind touching up often, this is great, and reapplying causes no caking issues (because it really just doesn't last so it's like you never had any on).

name: Budget P
review: I dont use a lot of foundation so I was looking for something that would go on smoothly and this was great. Wish they had more color variety but I thought it was great. Will definitely use it a lot in the summer when I'm looking for something light and easy to apply.

name: amber e
review:
This almost doesn't need to be blended - it applies and seems to melt right into the skin. Incredibly natural appearance, I can use this under my (middle-aged) eyes and it doesn't crease or cake or look like I'm wearing anything there. Most products are obvious and make that area look worse, not better. I haven't used it as a full face foundation, more as a spot-application to cover darkness, and it works well. I'm not sure I've ever tried a product quite like this.

I use a tiny concealer brush to apply this right where I need it. It's fantastic for anyone who needs light to medium natural looking coverage.

name: Rowie

Great when you're in a hurry. Dab on the nose, forehead and chin and blend with a sponge or your fingertips. Medium coverage in 10 seconds
Great for touch ups too
I will always bring this when I travel
